Lancaster.Reilly Brothers and Raub Building: Reilly Brothers and Raub Building is a historic commercial building located at Lancaster, Lancaster County, Pennsylvania. It was designed by noted Lancaster architect C. Emlen Urban and built in 1910–1911. It is a four- to five-story, "L"-shaped, steel frame structure clad in brick, pink granite, Indiana limestone, and copper in the Beaux-Arts style.
